  "text": "When S. cerevisiae cells were incubated in growth medium with FITC-dextran, the marker was found in the vacuoles, which appeared brightly stained (Fig. 1 A) . The vacuole, which may comprise as much as 25 % of the volume of the yeast cell [CITATION_1] , can be easily visualized by Nomarski optics (Fig. 1 D) . We have described earlier the internalization of FITC-dextran into the yeast vacuole using fluorescence microscopy [CITATION_2] .",
